text.tspan: Wildlife trade is quantified in terms of whole organism equivalents (WOE). For example, five skulls represent five
WOEs, whereas it's assumed that four ears are sourced from two animals and so represent two WOEs.
Source: Harfoot et al. (2018). Unveiling the patterns and trends in 40 years of global trade in CITES-listed wildlife.
